#, no-wrap
msgid "Slint Handbook (version 15.0)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: HandBook.adoc:9
#, no-wrap
msgid "Introduction to Slint"
msgstr "Introduksjon til Slint"

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:11
#, no-wrap
msgid "About Slint"
msgstr "Om Slint"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:14
msgid "Slint is a https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux_distribution[Linux distribution], based on http://www.slackware.com/[Slackware], polyglot, easy to install, versatile, beginner friendly and accessible to the visually impaired."
msgstr "Slint er en https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux_distribution[Linux distribution], basert på http://www.slackware.com/[Slackware], polyglo, enkelt å installere, allsidig, nybegynner vennlig og tilgjengelig for synshemmede."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:16
msgid "A Slint system is functional out of the box and can be tailored to fit most computing requirements."
msgstr "Et Slint-system er funksjonelt ut av boksen og kan tilpasses de fleste krav til datamaskin."

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "Features"
msgstr "Funksjoner"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:20
msgid "Two installation modes are proposed: Automatic (the installer prepare the drive chosen by the user and install Slint on it) and Manual (The installer format the Linux partition chosen by the user, format it and install Slint on it). The installer includes a documentation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:22
msgid "Slint is accessible to visually impaired users, with speech and braille, from installation to usage in a console as in graphical environments."
msgstr "Skarpestrek er tilgjengelig for brukere med synshemmede tale, mote og modige, fra installasjon til bruk i en konsoll som i grafiske miljøer."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:24
msgid "A wide assortment of software for servers, desktops, and laptops is installed in all Slint systems, which include two graphical desktop environments: MATE and LXQt, and lightweight window managers. MATE and LXQt provide easy access to all applications and system operations, with auto-mounting of removable devices, plus notifications of available updates of installed software, immediate Internet access, stopping, rebooting, and hibernating the system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:26
msgid "The language chosen will be used for internationalized applications."
msgstr "Det valgte språket skal brukes til internasjonaliserte applikasjoner."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:28
msgid "The Slint Dashboard centralizes access to hardware and system settings, packages, system tools, documentation and utilities."
msgstr "Slint-panelet sentraliserer tilgang til maskinvare- og systeminnstillinger, pakker, systemverktøy, dokumentasjon og hjelpeutstyr."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:30
msgid "Slint ships with many applications out of the box to create, edit, view and convert documents in various formats, communicate by email, text and audio chat, play audio and video, send and receive documents peer to peer, edit audio, video and graphical documents, develop applications. It is fully usable as a server on a console and using one of the several included desktops."
msgstr "Slinke skip med mange søknader ut av boksen om å skrive og lese og konvertere dokumenter i ulike formater, kommunisere via e-post, tekst og lyd-chat, spille av lyd og video, send og motta dokumenter kilde til kilde, rediger lyd, video og grafiske dokumenter, utviklingsprogrammer. Det kan brukes som en server på en konsoll og bruker en av de flere skrivebordene."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:32
msgid "Many applications are accessible to visually impaired users, a wide choice of TTS and associated voices is included, if you still need others they are easily installable, usable both in a textual environment (console) as well as on the desktop."
msgstr "Mange bruksområder er tilgjengelig for brukere med synshemmede, et bredt valg av TTS og tilhørende stemmer, hvis du fortsatt trenger andre er lett å installere, brukes både i tekstområder (konsoll) og i skrivebordet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:34
msgid "Several in-house tools ease administration and configuration of your Slint system."
msgstr "Flere interne verktøy letter administrasjonen og konfigureringen av Slint-systemet ditt."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:36
msgid "Many more applications are easily built installed as software packages through a simple command or a few clicks. Thousands of software packages are at your fingertips!"
msgstr "Mange flere applikasjoner bygges enkelt som programvarepakker gjennom en enkel kommando eller noen få klikk. Tusenvis av programvarepakker er fingeravtrykk!"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:38
msgid "Slint users are notified about upgrades of installed packages as soon as available, easily installed upon request. This keeps your system safe."
msgstr "Sline-brukere varsles om oppgraderinger av installerte pakker så snart som tilgjengelig, enkelt installert etter forespørsel. Dette holder systemet ditt trygt."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:40
msgid "Default preferred applications settings are provided and can be easily customized."
msgstr "Standard innstillinger for foretrukne applikasjoner er oppgitt, og kan lett tilpasses."

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:41
#, no-wrap
msgid "Content, versions and release model"
msgstr "Innhold, versjoner og utgivelsesmodeller."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:44
msgid "The Slint installer provides only a complete installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:46
msgid "Slint follows a \"semi-rolling\" release model, meaning that during the life cycle of a given version, in addition to updates as security fixes and major bug fixes, some software are selectively updated to bring enhancements, and added to bring new features. This is the case for software contributing to make Slint accessible to the blind, like screen readers."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:48
msgid "We recommend that users switch to a new version as soon as possible after its release. We recommend that they do a full backup of all data they want to keep followed by a an installation a new and a restoration of the backup."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:49
#, no-wrap
msgid "About this book, other sources of information"
msgstr "Om denne boken, andre informasjonskilder"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:52
msgid "This book is intended for the Slint newcomer whom it guides through its installation process and usage. The concepts and conventions specific to Slint and common in Linux distributions are presented and a glossary is annexed."
msgstr "Denne boken er ment for Slint-newcomer som den veileder gjennom sin installasjonsprosess og bruk. Begrepene og konvensjonene som gjelder spesielt for Slint og felles innenfor Linux-distribusjoner, presenteres og en ordliste er annullert."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:54
msgid "We try to accommodate folks coming from Windows or MacOS as users of another distribution like Ubuntu."
msgstr "Vi prøver å ta imot kunder som kommer fra Windows eller MacOS som brukere av en annen distribusjon, som Ubuntu."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:56
msgid "Documentation about installed software is generally available in a Slint system. We will state in this book how to access it."
msgstr "Dokumentasjon på installert programvare er vanligvis tilgjengelig i et Slint-system. Vi kommer til å vise i denne boken hvordan vi kan få tilgang til den."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:58
msgid "Other sources of information are available:"
msgstr "Andre kilder til informasjon er tilgjengelige:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:60
msgid "The information often provided in their website by the authors of software included in Slint."
msgstr "Forfatterne av programvare som er inkludert i Slint, gir ofte informasjonen på sine nettsider."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:61
msgid "http://docs.slackware.com/[The Slackware documentation project] and particularly its http://docs.slackware.com/howtos:start[HOWTO articles] Many are applicable directly to Slint, some adaptations and updates can be necessary."
msgstr "http://docs.slackware.com/[Slackware dokumentasjonsprosjekt] og spesielt http://docs.slackware.com/howtos:start[dens ] HOWTO artikler</a> Mange kan brukes direkte på Slint, Noen tilpasninger og oppdateringer kan være nødvendige."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:62
msgid "Beyond the Arch distribution, the ArchWiki provides often helpful article on software also shipped in Slint. For instance searching \"arch wiki mate\" leads to https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/MATE[this page about MATE]. Caveat: the information provided can need to be adapted as Slint and Arch differ on some regards. For instance Arch uses systemd as init system and a given software can be configured differently by default in Slint and Arch."
msgstr "Utover Arch distribusjonen tilbyr ArchWiki ofte en nyttig artikkel om programvare som også sendes i Slint. For eksempel kan \"arch wiki mate\" føye til https://wiki.archlinux.org/index.php/MATE[denne siden om MATE]. Caveat: Informasjonen som gis må tilpasses når Slint og Arch på noen måter er forskjellige. For eksempel kan Arch bruke system d som innfelt system og en gitt programvare konfigureres annerledes som standard i Slint og Arch."

#.  Support
#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:63
msgid "And of course an Internet search engine can often help find answers to questions and solutions to issues."
msgstr "En Internett-søkemotor kan selvsagt ofte bidra til å finne svar på spørsmål og løsninger på spørsmål."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:65
#, no-wrap
msgid "Support"
msgstr "Brukerstøtte"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:68
msgid "You can get help through these channels:"
msgstr "Du kan få hjelp gjennom disse kanalene:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:70
msgid "The Slint mailing list is the primary support channel. To register, email slint-request@freelists.org with as subject: 'subscribe' then answer the confirmation email that you will receive. Then, to know more email slint-request@freelists.org with as subject 'commands' or 'help'. After registration, email slint@freelists.org."
msgstr "The Slint mailing list is the primary support channel. For å registrere deg kan du slint-request@freelists.org med som tittel: 'abbon' og svare på bekreftelses-e-posten du vil motta. Deretter kan du vite mer e-post slint-request@freelists.org med emnet 'commands' eller 'help'. Etter registrering, send e-post slint@freelists.org."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:71
msgid "The archives of the mailing list are available https://www.freelists.org/archive/slint[here]."
msgstr "Arkivene på e-postlisten er tilgjengelige https://www.freelists.org/archive/slint[her]."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:72
msgid "On IRC: chat on the #slint channel, server irc.libera.chat, no registration needed."
msgstr "På IRC: chat på #slint kanalen, server irc.libera.chat, ingen registrering nødvendig."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:73
msgid "Mumble: server slint.fr (on appointment taken through another channel)."
msgstr "Mumble: server-slint.fr (ved avtale tatt gjennom en annen kanal)."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:74
msgid "The https://forum.salixos.org/viewforum.php?f=44[Slint forum] kindly hosted by our friends at Salix (another Slackware derivative). Registration needed."
msgstr "https://forum.salixos.org/viewforum.php?f=44[Slint forum] snille med våre venner på Salix (et annet Slackware derivater). Registrering kreves."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:77
msgid "To find out more, see the links under Information in the Slint Dashboard or just type: slint-doc in a terminal after installation."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "Translation and other contributions to the Slint project"
msgstr "Oversettelse og andre bidrag til Slint-prosjektet"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:81
msgid "Slint need translators! If you want to participate to the translation effort, read the instructions in https://slint.fr/doc/translate_slint.html[Translate Slint]."
msgstr "Linje trenger oversettere! Hvis du vil delta i oversettelsesarbeidet, kan du lese instruksjonene i https://slint.fr/doc/translate_slint.html[oversette Slint]."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:83
msgid "The translation files are hosted on https://crowdin.com/project/slint[Crowdin]."
msgstr "Oversettelsesfilene er vert på https://crowdin.com/project/slint[Crowdin]."

#.  Acknowledgments
#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:85
msgid "If you want to contribute to Slint for other tasks, just post in the mailing list or drop a line to: didieratslintdotfr. Of course translators are welcome on the mailing list too!"
msgstr "Hvis du vil bidra til Slint for andre oppgaver, bare skriv i postlisten eller send en linje for å dieratslintdotfr. Av kurs oversettere er velkommen på maillisten også!"

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:87
#, no-wrap
msgid "Acknowledgments"
msgstr "Godkjennelser"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:90
msgid "The Slint project exists mainly through to the hard work of the Slint translators and other contributors, thanks to all of you!"
msgstr "Slint-prosjektet eksisterer hovedsakelig gjennom til det harde arbeidet til punktoversettere og andre bidragsytere, takket være alle deg!"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:92
msgid "Thanks to George Vlahavas for his advice and tools, to the contributors to the SlackBuilds.org project, who help building so many additional software."
msgstr "Takket være George Vlahavas for sine råd og verktøy, bidragsyterne til SlackBuilds.org prosjektet, som hjelper med å bygge så mye tilleggsprogramvare."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:94
msgid "Slint is based on Slackware, brought by Patrick J. Volkerding and contributors. Thanks! I encourage all Slint users to contribute to Slackware funding, and also to donate to the Salix project."
msgstr "Slint er basert på Slackware, skapt av Patrick J. Volkerding og bidragsytere. Takk! Jeg oppfordrer alle Slint-brukere til å bidra til Slackware finansiering og også til å donere til Salix-prosjektet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:96
msgid "The Slint repositories are kindly hosted for free by Darren 'Tadgy' Austin. I encourage all Slint users to contribute to funding the host https://slackware.uk/"
msgstr "Arkitekturene fra Slint-depotet blir anskaffet av Darren Tadgy Austin. Jeg oppfordrer alle Slint-brukere til å bidra til å finansiere verten https://slackware.uk/"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "Links for financial contributions:\n"
"https://www.patreon.com/slackwarelinux[Become a Slackware patron] or https://paypal.me/volkerdi[Support Slackware]\n"
"Follow the links on top of http://slackware.uk/slint/x86_64/slint-15.0/[this page] to support Slackware UK\n"
"https://salixos.org/donations.html[Donations to Salix]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ==
#: HandBook.adoc:102
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install Slint"
msgstr "Installer Slint"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:105
msgid "This part of the HandBook walks through the process of downloading Slint, verifying the ISO image with a check-sum, writing the ISO to an installation medium, partitioning your hard disk, and briefly describes the installation process."
msgstr "Denne delen av håndboken går gjennom å laste ned Slint, og verifiserer ISO-bildet med en sjekksum, skriving av ISO til et installasjonsmedium, partisjonering av din harde disk, og beskriver kort tid monteringsprosessen."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:106
#, no-wrap
msgid "Requirements"
msgstr "Krav"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:109
msgid "The current Slint version can be installed on computers meeting these requirements:"
msgstr "Den nåværende Slint-versjonen kan installeres på datamaskiner som oppfyller disse kravene:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:111
msgid "Architecture: x86_64 (64-bit CPU), also known as AMD64"
msgstr "Arkitekt: x86_64 (64-bit CPU), også kjent som AMD64"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:112
msgid "In Auto partitioning mode a disk drive of size at least 50G"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:113
msgid "In Manual partitioning mode a partition of type Linux of size at least 50G, an EFI system partition and/or a BIOS boot partition on the same disk drive. The EFI partition is mandatory if the machine boots in EFI mode, the BIOS boot partition if the machine boots in Legacy mode, having both is better to allow swictching between EFI and Legacy modes."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:114
msgid "Slint can be installed on these kinds of drives: hard drives, SSD, NVME, eMMC, USB sticks, SD cards (preferably in USB enclosures)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:115
msgid "RAM: at least 2G"
msgstr "AM: minst 2G"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:116
msgid "a DVD drive or an USB slot available, with ability of the firmware to boot a DVD or USB stick. A blank DVD or a 5G or more USB stick can be used as installation media"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:118
msgid "Secure boot should be disabled to install Slint."
msgstr "Sikker oppstart bør være deaktivert for å installere Slint."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:119
#, no-wrap
msgid "Features of the installer"
msgstr "Funksjoner til installatøren"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:122
msgid "The installer is a \"live system\", running in memory: it will not modify an installed system, unless and until you tell it to."
msgstr "Installatøren er et \"direkte system\", som kjører i minnet: den vil ikke endre et installert system, med mindre du forteller det det."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:123
msgid "For blind users the installer is fully usable with Braille, and speech using the Speakup screen reader."
msgstr "For blinde brukere er montøren fullstendig brukbar med blindeskrift, og taleanrop ved hjelp av skjermleseren."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:124
msgid "It includes all needed utilities to prepare the needed partitions prior to an installation in Manual partitioning mode."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:125
msgid "The Auto mode of installation instead just needs user to answering questions and provide a contextual help about them."
msgstr "Automodus for installasjon i stedet trenger bare en bruker for å svare på spørsmål og gi en kontekstbasert hjelp med dem."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:126
msgid "If installed alone on a removable device connected through USB, Slint is portable, i.e. usable on any computer able to boot off an USB drive beyond the computer used to install it. For instance if installing on an USB stick you can just plug the stick in a computer to run it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:127
msgid "The installer can encrypt the drive where Slint is installed alone. This prevents the steal of data it contains in case of loss or theft of the machine, or of a removable drive."
msgstr "Installatøren kan kryptere stasjonen der Slint er installert alene. Dette forhindrer stjålet fra data den inneholder ved tap eller tyveri fra maskinen, eller av en flyttbar stasjon."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:128
msgid "Slint can be installed in its own drive, and in manual partitioning mode alongside another system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:129
#, no-wrap
msgid "Preparation"
msgstr "Forberedelse"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:134
#, no-wrap
msgid "<<download_and_verify,Download and verify a Slint ISO image>>\n"
"<<write_the_iso,Write the ISO image on an Installation Medium>>\n"
"<<prepare_partitions_for_Slint,Optionally, prepare partitions for Slint>>"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:136
#, no-wrap
msgid "Download and verify a Slint ISO image"
msgstr "Last ned og verifiser et ISO-bilde av Slint"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:139
msgid "The latest version of the Slint distribution is 15.0"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:141
msgid "The latest installation ISO image is always available in https://slackware.uk/slint/x86_64/slint-15.0/iso[this directory]"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:143
msgid "This ISO image can also be downloaded using a Torrent Client from this page:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:145
msgid "https://seedbox.slackware.uk/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:147
msgid "The link to the torrent, after the label \"Slint Torrents\", is:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:149
msgid "https://seedbox.slackware.uk/torrents/slint64-15.0-5-iso.torrent"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:151
msgid "A magnet is also provided."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:155
msgid "As long as you are running Slint version 15.0 there is no need to re-install when a new ISO is provided, as it only brings new features of the installer and new or and upgraded packages that you can also get keeping your system up to date."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:158
msgid "The file name of the ISO indicated below is just an example, that you will adapt to the current name when downloading."
msgstr "Filnavnet til ISO angitt nedenfor er et eksempel, du vil tilpasse deg gjeldende navn når du laster ned."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:160
msgid "If you are running Windows, an Internet search with as argument \"check sha256sum windows\" will tell you how to proceed."
msgstr "Hvis du kjører Windows, vil et internett med som argument «sjekk sha256sum vinduer» fortelle deg hvordan du kan fortsette."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:162
msgid "If you are running Linux you can download the ISO image and its sha256 checksum typing:"
msgstr "Hvis du kjører Linux, kan du laste ned ISO-bildet og kontrollsummen av dette kan du skrive inn:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:165
#, no-wrap
msgid "wget https://slackware.uk/slint/x86_64/slint-15.0/iso/slint64-15.0-5.iso\n"
"wget https://slackware.uk/slint/x86_64/slint-15.0/iso/slint64-15.0-5.iso.sha256\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:168
msgid "To check the integrity of the downloaded files type this command:"
msgstr "For å kontrollere integriteten til de nedlastede filene, skriv denne kommandoen: sha256sum -c slint64-14.2.1.4.iso.sha256 skal resultatet være: OK"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:170
#, no-wrap
msgid "sha256sum -c slint64-15.0-5.iso.sha256\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:174
#, no-wrap
msgid "The result should be : OK\n"
"Else, redo the downloads."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:176
#, no-wrap
msgid "Write the ISO image on an Installation Medium"
msgstr "Skriv ISO-bildet på en installasjon Medium"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:179
msgid "You can use either a DVD or an USB stick as installation media."
msgstr "Du kan bruke enten DVD eller USB-enhet som installasjonsmedium."

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:183
msgid "You can just store the ISO image in the first partition of a Ventoy USB stick."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:185
msgid "In this case at the beginning of installation the installer will request that you mount this partition, then mount the ISO itself."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: HandBook.adoc:188
#, no-wrap
msgid "Make a Bootable USB Stick"
msgstr "Lag en Båtbar USB-pinne"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:191
msgid "On a ++Linux++ system, plug in the USB stick, and check it's name with the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:194
#, no-wrap
msgid "lsblk -o model,name,size,fstype,mountpoint\n"
msgstr "lsblk -o modell,name,size,fstype,mountpoint\n"

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:199
msgid "Carefully review the output of the command to make sure that you will not type the name of a hard disk partition instead of the name of your USB stick. All previous content of the USB stick or a mistaken hard disk partition will be **LOST** and **IRRECOVERABLE**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:202
msgid "Let's assume that the name of the USB stick be /dev/sdb. It could be named otherwise, so don't copy blindly the following command. The command syntax to write the Slint ISO to a USB stick that resides at /dev/sdb is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:205
#, no-wrap
msgid "dd if=slint64-15.0-5.iso of=/dev/sdb bs=1M status=progress && sync\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:210
msgid "The above command assumes **if=** points to the path of the Slint ISO and **of=** points to the name of the USB stick. These values may differ on your system."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:213
msgid "On ++Windows++ use an application like http://rufus.akeo.ie/[Rufus]. It is free and open source."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: HandBook.adoc:215
#, no-wrap
msgid "Make a Bootable DVD Disc"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:218
msgid "On a ++Linux++ system insert the DVD and type the following command:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:221
#, no-wrap
msgid "xorriso -as cdrecord -v dev=/dev/sr0 -eject slint64-15.0-5.iso\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:224
msgid "Be sure to enter the full path to the Slint ISO on your filesystem."
msgstr "Sørg for å skrive inn hele filbanen til Slint ISO på filsystemet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:226
