#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:464
msgid "The installer asks a question, you type the answer and confirm it by pressing Enter."
msgstr "Installatøren stiller et spørsmål, du skriv svaret og bekreft det ved å trykke på Enter."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:465
msgid "The installer displays a menu of choices or options: you select one of them using the up and down arrow keys, then confirm your choice by pressing Enter, or cancel by pressing Escape."
msgstr "Installatøren viser menyen til valg eller alternativer: Du velger en av dem ved hjelp av piltastene opp og ned, så bekreft ditt valg ved å trykke på Enter eller Avbryt ved å trykke på Escape."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:466
msgid "The installer displays information in a pager. Then use arrow keys to read the next or previous line, press space to display the next page, Q to stop reading the document."
msgstr "Installasjonsprogrammet viser informasjon i en pager. Bruk deretter piltastene for å lese neste eller forrige linje, trykk på mellomrom for å vise neste side, Q for å stoppe avlesningen av dokumentet."

#.  Encryption
#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:469
#, no-wrap
msgid "Slint with an encrypted root partition."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:475
msgid "In Auto mode the installer proposes to encrypt the root system partition. If you agree, at each boot the GRUB boot loader will ask you the passphrase that you will have typed during installation to unlock the drive, before displaying the boot menu. Be aware that unlocking the drive will take a few seconds (about ten seconds)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:479
msgid "Having an encrypted root system prevents the steal of data it contains in case of loss or theft of the machine, or of a removable drive. But this won't protect you if the computer stays running and unattended, only if the machine has been switched off completely!"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:482
msgid "During installation the Slint system partition will be encrypted, and also the additional partition that you may request."
msgstr "Under installasjonen vil systempartisjonen fra Slint bli kryptert, og også ekstra partisjon du ber om."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:485
msgid "A Slint system (or root) partition will the be named: /dev/mapper/cryproot once opened, if it has been encrypted."
msgstr "Et «Slint-system» (eller root) partisjonen vil bli namnet: /dev/mapper/cryproot når er åpnet, hvis den er kryptert."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:487
msgid "This is shown by this command:"
msgstr "Dette vises ved denne kommandoen:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:490
#, no-wrap
msgid "lsblk -lpo name,fstype,mountpoint | grep /$\n"
msgstr "lsblk -lpo name,fstype,mountpoint θ grep /$\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:493
msgid "Which gives an output like:"
msgstr "Som gir en utlysning som:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:495
#, no-wrap
msgid "/dev/mapper/cryptroot ext4    /\n"
msgstr "/dev/mapper/cryptroot ext4 /\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:498
msgid "This command instead:"
msgstr "Denne kommandoen i stedet:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:501
#, no-wrap
msgid "lsblk -lpo name,fstype,mountpoint | grep /dev/sda3\n"
msgstr "lsblk -lpo navn,fstype,montpoint θ grep /dev/sda3\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:504
msgid "gives:"
msgstr "sjefer:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:507
#, no-wrap
msgid "/dev/sda3             cryptoLUKS\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:513
msgid "/dev/sda3 is now a \"raw\" partition that includes the so called \"LUKS header\" that you will never need nor ever should access directly. It hosts all that is needed to encrypt or decrypt the partition /dev/mapper/cryptroot, which actually hosts your data (in this example the Slint system)."
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:519
msgid "If you forget the passphrase all data in the drive will be irrecoverably lost! So write down or record this passphrase and put the record on a safe place as soon as done."
msgstr "Hvis du glemmer passordfrasen vil alle data i stasjonen være uopprettelig tapt! So write down or record this passphrase and put the record on a safe place as soon as done."

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:522
msgid "Drives die. If that happens and it is encrypted your data will be lost.  So, regularly back up your important data is not optional."
msgstr "Stasjoner dør. Hvis det skjer, og det er kryptert vil dataene dine gå tapt.  Det er derfor ikke valgfritt å sikkerhetskopiere viktige data."

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:525
msgid "Also, make a backup copy of the luks header which you can restore in case the luks partition is damaged for any reason. The command could be in our example:"
msgstr "Sørg også for å lage en sikkerhetskopi av luks-overskriften som du vil kunne gjenopprette lukspartisjonen ble skadet av en eller annen grunn. Kommandoen kan ha vært i vårt eksempel:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:527
#, no-wrap
msgid "luksHeaderBackup /dev/sda3 --header-backup-file <file>\n"
msgstr "luksHeaderBackup /dev/sda3 --header-backup-fil <file>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:529
msgid "where <file> is the name of the backup file, that you will store in a safe place."
msgstr "der <file> er navnet på sikkerhetskopien, som du vil lagre på et trygt sted."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:531
msgid "Then would you need to restore the backup, type:"
msgstr "Da må du gjenopprette sikkerhetskopien, typen:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:533
#, no-wrap
msgid "luksHeaderRestore /dev/sda3 --header-backup-file <file>\n"
msgstr "luksHeaderRestore /dev/sda3 --header-backup-fil <file>\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:538
msgid "Don't resize a partition of an encrypted drive as after that it would be definitively locked and all the data it contains will be lost! If you really need more space, you will need to backup all the files that you want to keep, then install anew and restore the backed up files."
msgstr "Don't endre størrelse en partisjon på en kryptert disk som etter at det ville være definitivt låst og alle dataene den inneholder vil gå tapt! Hvis du virkelig trenger mer plass, må du sikkerhetskopiere alle filene du vil beholde, Installer så om og gjenopprett de sikkerhetskopierte filene."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:541
msgid "Choose a strong passphrase, so that it would take too much time for a robber to discover for it to be worthwhile."
msgstr "Velg et sterkt passord slik at det tar for mye tid til at en robber oppdages for at den skal være verd."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:547
msgid "Never ever fiddle with the so-called \"LUKS header\" located on the raw partition (the third one, like e.g. /dev/sda3 for the raw partition on top of the Slint system partition). Practically: don't create a file system in this partition, don't make it part of a RAID array and generally don't write to it: all data would be irrecoverably lost!"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:550
msgid "To avoid weak passphrases the installer requires that the passphrase include:"
msgstr "For å unngå svake adgangsfraser krever montøren at passordet omfatter:"

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:552
msgid "At least 8 characters."
msgstr "Minst 8 tegn."

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:553
msgid "Only non accented lower case and capital letters, digits from 0 to 9, space and following punctuation characters:"
msgstr "Bare små bokstaver og store bokstaver, sifre fra 0 til 9, mellomrom og følgende tegn til tegn:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:556
#, no-wrap
msgid " ' ! \" # $ % & ( ) * + , - . / : ; < = > ? @ [ \\ ] ^ _ ` { | } ~\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:560
msgid "This guarantees that even a new keyboard will have all characters needed to type the passphrase."
msgstr "Dette garanterer at selv et nytt tastatur har alle nødvendige tegn for å skrive passordet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:562
msgid "At least one digit, one lower case letter, one capital letter and one punctuation character."
msgstr "Minst ett siffer, én liten bokstav, en stor bokstav og ett punktum."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:569
msgid "GRUB assumes that \"us\" keyboard is in use when you type the passphrase.  For this reason, if during installation you use an other keyboard map, before asking the passphrase the installer will set the keyboard map to \"us\", and after having recorded it restore the previously used one. In this case the installer will also spell each typed character of the passphrase, as it may differ from the one written on the key."
msgstr "GRUB forutsetter at \"us\"-tastaturet brukes når du skriver inn passhrase.  Av denne grunn, hvis du under installasjonen bruker et annet tastaturkart, før hvis du spør passordfrase vil installasjonsprogrammet sette tastaturkartet til \"us\", og etter å ha registrert det gjenopprettet den tidligere brukte. I dette tilfellet vil installasjonsprogrammet også stave for hvert av de typede tegnene i adgangskassen, siden det kan avviker fra det som er skrevet på nøkkelen."

