#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1682
#, no-wrap
msgid "Kernel upgrades"
msgstr "Kjerne oppgraderinger"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1685
msgid "New kernels are provided whenever necessary, either to bring security fixes or enhancements."
msgstr "Nye kantinere tilbys ved behov, enten for å bringe sikkerhetskorrigeringer eller forbedringer."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1687
msgid "Usually no manual intervention from the user is necessary when this happens, but it can be useful to know how the kernel upgrade is done and what to do if something unexpected occurs."
msgstr "Vanligvis er ingen manuell intervensjon fra brukeren nødvendig når dette skjer, men det kan være nyttig å vite hvordan kjerne- oppgraderingen gjennomføres, og hva du må gjøre dersom noe uventet oppstår."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1689
msgid "Several packages include files associated with each kernel, namely: kernel-generic, kernel-modules, kernel-source, kernel headers. kernel-source and kernel-headers include files used to build software, only kernel-generic and kernel-modules are needed to run a Slint system."
msgstr "Flere pakker er filer tilknyttet hver kjerne det vil si: kernelgeneriske, kernelmoduler, kjerneløse, kernelsource, kjerne hoder. kernelkilde og kernel-overskrifter omfatter filer som brukes til å bygge programvare, og bare kernel-generiske og kernel-moduler er nødvendige for å kjøre et Slint-system."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1691
msgid "The package kernel-modules ships files called modules, which are pieces of code that are \"plugged in\" the kernel to provide a specific feature or handle a specific hardware."
msgstr "Pakkernelmodulene sender filer som kalles moduler, som er en del av koden som \"plugget inne\" kjelen til å oppgi en bestemt funksjon eller håndtere en bestemt beslag."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1695
msgid "As soon as both a kernel package and the associated kernel-modules package are installed, the script /sbin/wrapupgradepkg builds an <<initrd,initrd>> associated with this kernel (with modules taken from the package kernel-modules) and installs it alongside the kernel in the /boot directory."
msgstr "Så snart både en kjerne pakke og den tilknyttede kjernelods-pakken er installert, skriptet /sbin/wrapupdepkg bygger en <<initrd, tomme>> som er knyttet til denne kjernen (med moduler tatt fra pakkernel-moduler) og installerer det sammen med kjernen i /boot mappen."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1697
msgid "Then previous kernels (not in use at time of upgrade) are removed."
msgstr "Deretter tas tidligere kjerner (ikke i bruk ved oppgradering) fjernet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1699
msgid "Then the script updates the GRUB configuration file /boot/grub/grub.cfg, read by the OS loader to build the boot menu."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1701
msgid "This boot menu will then include at least two boot entries each indicating, to indicating a kernel and its associated initrd to use. From the top:"
msgstr "Denne oppstartsmenyen vil deretter inkludere minst to oppstartsoppføringer for hver indikasjon, for å indikere en kjerne og dens tilknyttede plass som skal brukes. Fra toppen:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1703
msgid "A boot entry to start Slint using the new kernel that has just been installed."
msgstr "En oppstartsoppføring for å starte Slint ved å bruke den nye kjernen som nettopp er installert."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1704
msgid "A boot entry to start Slint using the kernel in use at time of upgrade."
msgstr "En oppstartsoppføring for å starte Slint ved å bruke kjernen i bruk på oppgraderingstidspunktet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1707
msgid "This provide kind of a \"safety net\" in case Slint wouldn't boot with the new kernel: in this case just arrow down once when the boot menu is displayed to start Slint with the previous kernel"
msgstr "Denne tilbyr type \"sikkerhetsnett\" i tilfelle Slint wouldn't oppstart med den nye kjernen: i så fall bare pilen en en gang når oppstartsmenyen er vist for å starte streken med den forrige kjernen"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1709
msgid "You can preview the new boot menu before rebooting, typing as root:"
msgstr "Du kan forhåndsvise den nye oppstartsmenyen før du starter på nytt, og skrive som root:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1711
#, no-wrap
msgid "grub-emu\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1714
msgid "Then an emulated or \"fake\" boot menu is displayed, with the same layout as the real one which will displayed at next boot."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1716
msgid "You can navigate in it with the down and up arrow keys to highlight (put the focus on)  a boot entry of which you can display the details pressing 'e'. You can go back to the menu pressing Escape."
msgstr "Du kan navigere i den med ned- og opp-piltastene for å fremheve (sette fokus) en oppstartsoppføring, som du kan vise detaljene ved å trykke 'e'. Du kan gå tilbake til menyen ved å trykke Escape."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1718
msgid "To exit from grub-emu press c then type *exit* and press Enter."
msgstr "For å gå ut fra et papir trykk c deretter type *avkjør* og trykk på Enter."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1720
msgid "Alternatively you can type as root:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1722
#, no-wrap
msgid "list_boot_entries\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1725
#, no-wrap
msgid "Get additional applications"
msgstr "Hent tillegg-applikasjoner"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1729
msgid "The easiest and recommended way to get additional applications not shipped in Slint is to use slapt-get or its graphical front-end gslapt.  This gives you access to all packages in repositories enabled in /etc/slapt-get/slapt-getrc by default in addition to the Slint repository: +"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1731
msgid "The Slackware repository, with dependency information: SOURCE=https://slackware.uk/salix/x86_64/slackware-15.0/:OFFICIAL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1732
msgid "The Salix extra repository, fed for Salix distribution by its maintainer George Vlahavas aka gapan but usable in Slint as well: SOURCE=https://slackware.uk/salix/x86_64/extra-15.0/:OFFICIAL"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1734
msgid "If the application you want is not installed and also not available in one of the repositories enabled in /etc/slapt-get/slapt-getrc you could make a package for it, using build material provided by volunteers @ https://slackbuilds.org. To know how-to proceed, read https://slackbuilds.org/howto/ and https://slackbuilds.org/faq/"
msgstr "Hvis applikasjonen du vil er ikke installert og ikke tilgjengelig i et av kodelagrene aktivert i /etc/slapt-get/slapt-getrc kan du lage en pakke for det, bruke byggemateriale fra frivillige @ https://slackbuilds.org. For å vite hva som skal gjøres, les https://slackbuilds.org/howto/ og https://slackbuilds.org/faq/"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1736
msgid "The packages built this way should be compatible with Slint."
msgstr "Pakker utført på denne måten bør være kompatible med Slint."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1738
msgid "The application *slapt-src* and its graphical front-end *sourcery* allows you to build and install packages using the build material provided at https://slackbuilds.org, to be used as root or using sudo."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1740
msgid "We will describe slapt-src in more details."
msgstr "Vi skal beskrive smalt-src i flere detaljer."

#. type: delimited block =
#: HandBook.adoc:1744
msgid "Pre-built packages for most applications that can be built with slap-src or sourcery are available in the Salix extra repository. Preferably install these pre-built packages using slapt-get or gslapt, unless you need specific build options or a different version than the one provided."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title =====
#: HandBook.adoc:1747
#, no-wrap
msgid "Usage of slapt-srcrc"
msgstr "Bruk av skrånende srcrc"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1750
msgid "The default configuration script for slapt-src is /etc/slapt-get/slap-srcrc and has this content:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1754
#, no-wrap
msgid "BUILDDIR=/var/lib/slapt-src\n"
"PKGEXT=txz\n"
"SOURCE=https://slackbuilds.org/slackbuilds/15.0/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1756
msgid "So:"
msgstr "Til:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1758
msgid "All build material and packages will go in /var/lib/slapt-src"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1759
msgid "The names of packages built end in .txz"
msgstr "Navnene på pakkene som er bygget i txz"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1760
msgid "The build material is fetched from the repository https://slackbuilds.org/slackbuilds/15.0/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1762
msgid "Here is the output of the command *slapt-src --help*:"
msgstr "Her er resultatet av kommandoen *slapt-src --help*:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1783
#, no-wrap
msgid "Usage: slapt-src [option(s)] [action] [slackbuild(s)]\n"
"  -u, --update           update local cache of remote slackbuilds\n"
"  -U, --upgrade-all      upgrade all installed slackbuilds\n"
"  -l, --list             list available slackbuilds\n"
"  -e, --clean            clean build directory\n"
"  -s, --search           search available slackbuilds\n"
"  -w, --show             show specified slackbuilds\n"
"  -i, --install          fetch, build, and install the specified slackbuild(s)\n"
"  -b, --build            only fetch and build the specified slackbuild(s)\n"
"  -f, --fetch            only fetch the specified slackbuild(s)\n"
"  -v, --version\n"
"  -h, --help\n"
" Options:\n"
"  -y, --yes              do not prompt\n"
"  -t, --simulate         show what will be done\n"
"  -c, --config=FILE      use the specified configuration file\n"
"  -n, --no-dep           do not look for dependencies\n"
"  -p, --postprocess=CMD  run specified command on generated package\n"
"  -B, --build-only       applicable only to --upgrade-all\n"
"  -F, --fetch-only       applicable only to --upgrade-all\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1786
msgid "Let's comment some of these options:"
msgstr "La's kommentere noen av disse mulighetene:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1788
msgid "Use -u or --update every time to update the list of packages that can be built and installed. This commands writes the file /tmp/slapt-src/slackbuilds_data, replacing the previous one case occurring."
msgstr "Bruk -u eller --oppdatering hver gang for å oppdatere listen over pakker som kan bygges og installeres. Dette kommandoene skriver filen /tmp/slapt-src/slackbuilds_data, og erstatter det foregående et tilfelle som skjer."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1789
msgid "Use -e to save space on disk, removing most files in /tmp/slapt-src/"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1790
msgid "do *not* use -U except to list the possible upgrades or downgrades, without confirming: confirming would lead to replace all Slint packages by one at another version if available in the remote repository, possibly breaking software not compatible with this other version."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1791
msgid "-i can also upgrade a package already installed from https://slackbuilds.org, if a the maintainer of the SlackBuild script has upgraded it, changing the VERSION variable."
msgstr "-i kan også oppgradere en pakke som allerede er installert fra https://slackbuilds.orgvedlikeholder SlackBuild-skriptet har oppgradert det, kan du endre VERSION-variabelen."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1792
msgid "Use -f to only download the files in https://slackbuilds.org for the target software. This can be useful if you want to check build material, or customize the build. For instance let's assume you want to fetch the build material for the software *mxml*. The command below gives some information about the software and which files are stored in https://slackbuilds.org for it:"
msgstr "Bruk -f for å bare laste ned filene i https://slackbuilds.org for målprogramvaren. Dette kan være nyttig hvis du vil sjekke byggemateriale, eller tilpasse bygningen. For eksempel la's anta at du ønsker å hente byggematerialet for programvare *mxml*. Kommandoen nedenfor gir noe informasjon om programvaren og hvilke filer som lagres i https://slackbuilds.org for den:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1804
#, no-wrap
msgid "slapt-src --show mxml\n"
"SlackBuild Name: mxml\n"
"SlackBuild Version: 3.1\n"
"SlackBuild Category: libraries/mxml/\n"
"SlackBuild Description: mxml (Lightweight xml parsing library)\n"
"SlackBuild Files:\n"
" README\n"
" mxml.SlackBuild\n"
" mxml.info\n"
" slack-desc\n"
msgstr "slapt-src --show mxml\n"
"SlackBuild Name: mxml\n"
"SlackBuild versjon: 3.\n"
"SlackBuild Kategori: biblioteker/mxml/\n"
"SlackBuild beskrivelse: mxml (lett-vekt xml parsing library)\n"
"SlackBuild Filer:\n"
" README\n"
" mxml. lackBuild\n"
" mxml.info\n"
" slack-desc\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1807
msgid "Now fetch theses files and also the source archive from upstream repository with the next command:"
msgstr "Hent nå disse filene og også kildearkivet fra oppstrøms depotet med neste kommando:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1810
#, no-wrap
msgid "slapt-get -f mxml\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1813
msgid "Knowing from the output of the previous command that the files are stored in the subdirectory libraries/mxml, you can check which files have been downloaded with this command:"
msgstr "Kjenner fra utdata av forrige kommando om at filene lagres i undermappens biblioteker/mxml, du kan sjekke hvilke filer som er lastet ned med denne kommandoen:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1820
#, no-wrap
msgid "ls -1 /var/lib/slapt-src/libraries/mxml\n"
"mxml-3.1.tar.gz\n"
"mxml.SlackBuild\n"
"mxml.info\n"
"slack-desc\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1822
msgid "Use -b if you want to build a package but not install it yet. In the example above it will be stored in /tmp/slapt-src/libraries/mxml, so you will be able to install it afterwards just typing:"
msgstr "Bruk -b hvis du vil lage en pakke, men ikke installer den ennå. I eksemplet ovenfor vil det bli lagret i /tmp/slapt-src/libraries/mxml, så du kan installere det bare etter:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1825
#, no-wrap
msgid "upgradepkg --install-new /tmp/slapt-src/libraries/mxml/xml*txz\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1828
msgid "Use -c if you want to use a custom configuration file instead of the default one /etc/slapt-get/slap-getrc"
msgstr "Bruk -c hvis du vil bruke en egendefinert konfigurasjonsfil i stedet for standard en /etc/slapt-get/slap-getrc"

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:1829
#, no-wrap
msgid "Manage users and groups"
msgstr "Administrer brukere og grupper."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1832
msgid "Two commands are provided to manage users and groups:"
msgstr "To kommandoer tilbys for å administrere brukere og grupper:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1834
msgid "The _usersetup_ command (TUI)"
msgstr "Kommandoen _bruker_ (TUI)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1835
msgid "The _gtkusersetup_ command (GUI), with an icon in the Slint Control Center, System category)"
msgstr "_gtkusersetup_ kommando (GUI), med et ikon i Slint Control Center, Systemkategori)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1837
msgid "These commands allow you to add or delete users and groups of users, and add users to groups."
msgstr "Disse kommandoene lar deg legge til eller slette brukere og grupper av brukere, og legge til brukere i grupper."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1839
msgid "Bear in mind that each user account is associated by default to its on space in the /home directory. For instance if you add a user *leonie*, a /home/leonie folder will be created, to which only this user (and root) will be allowed to access."
msgstr "Vær oppmerksom på at hver brukerkonto er tilknyttet som standard på grupperommet i /home katalogen. Hvis du for eksempel legger til en bruker *leonie*, opprettes en /home/leonie mappe. hvem bare denne brukeren (og root) skal få tilgang til."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:1840
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change the default language of the system"
msgstr "Endre standardspråket for systemet"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1843
msgid "Two commands are provided for that:"
msgstr "Det leveres to kommandoer for at:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1845
msgid "The _localesetup_ command (TUI)."
msgstr "_localesetup_ kommando (TUI)."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1846
msgid "The _gtklocalesetup_ command (GUI), with an icon in the Slint Control Center, Settings category."
msgstr "Kommandoen _gtklocalesetup_ (GUI), med et ikon i Slint Control Center, Innstillingskategori."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1848
msgid "Bear in mind that this settings changes the language used by the applications' interfaces if they are internationalized, not the keyboard map (see below)."
msgstr "Vær oppmerksom på at denne innstillingen endrer språket som brukes av programmenes grensesnitt dersom de internasjonaliseres, ikke tastaturkartet (se nedenfor)."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1850
msgid "Also, localized packages (if available) matching the language chosen have been already installed at end of Slint installation. If you change the default language afterwards, you will need to install the corresponding localized packages if you want."
msgstr "Også lokaliserte pakker (hvis tilgjengelig) som samsvarer med språket du har valgt har allerede blitt installert på slutten av Slint-installasjonen. Hvis du endrer standard språk i etterpå må du installere de lokaliserte pakkene hvis du ønsker."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1852
msgid "Localized means \"provided in a given locale\", the locale being a language plus peculiarities associated to a geographic area. For instance Portuguese spoken in Portugal and Brazil differ. In the localized packages names, l10n is an abbreviation of \"localization\" meaning \"letter l, 10 other letters, letter n\"."
msgstr "Lokaliteten betyr at «gitt lokalitet» er et språk pluss panserventikk knyttet til et geografisk område. For eksempel snakket portugisisk i Portugal og Brasil forskjellig. I de lokaliserte pakkenavnene er l10n en forkortelse for \"lokalisering\" betyr \"bokstav, 10 andre bokstaver, bokstav n\"."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1854
msgid "Localized packages are included for many languages. Their name include the base package name, a hyphen, then the language code. We list below the base names of the localized packages:"
msgstr "Lokaliserte pakker er inkludert for mange språk. Deres navn inkluderer basispakkenavn, en bindestrek, så språkkoden. Vi liste oss under basisnavnene på de lokaliserte pakkene:"

#. type: Table
#: HandBook.adoc:1860
#, no-wrap
msgid "| Base package name | Description\n"
"| aspell | word lists for spell check\n"
"| libreoffice-l0n | localized LibreOffice office suite\n"
"| libreoffice-help | localized help for LibreOffice\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1864
#, no-wrap
msgid "To find a localized package, type in a terminal emulator as root (example for libreoffice-l10n):\n"
"`spi libreoffice-l10n`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1867
#, no-wrap
msgid "This will display the list of all localized LibreOffice package. Find the one you want and install it. For instance for Persian the language code is `fa` (short for Farsi), so to install it type:\n"
"`spi -i libreoffice-l0n-fa`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1869
msgid "If you prefer you can use `gslapt`. Then, type the package name in the search field to display all localized libreoffice packages."
msgstr "Hvis du foretrekker kan du bruke `gslapt`. Deretter, skriv inn pakkenavnet i søkefeltet for å vise alle lokaliserte libreoffice pakker."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:1870
#, no-wrap
msgid "Change the keyboard map"
msgstr "Endre tastatur kartet"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1873
msgid "You can change the default keymap used in graphical mode using:"
msgstr "Du kan endre standard tastaturoppsett i grafisk modus ved hjelp av:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1875
msgid "The _keyboardsetup_ command (TUI)"
msgstr "_tastatur_ kommando (TUI)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1876
msgid "The _gtkkeyboardsetup_ command (GUI), with an icon in the Slint Control Center, Hardware category."
msgstr "Kommandoen _gtkkeyboardsetup_ (GUI), med et ikon i Slint Kontrollsenter og Hardware-kategorien."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1878
msgid "These commands also allow you to choose if numlock should be enabled when the system is started, and if the SCIM (input method) should be enabled at system startup."
msgstr "Disse kommandoene lar deg også velge om numlock skal være aktivert når systemet startes, og hvis SCIM (input-metode) bør være aktivert ved systemoppstart."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1880
msgid "If you use a window manager with a panel, you can also make this setting through a right click on the keyboard applet (displayed by default as the two letters language code of the keyboard map in use)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1882
msgid "On the command line but still for the graphical mode use instead the command `setxbmap`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1885
#, no-wrap
msgid "For instance to set the keyboard layout to Ukrainian in graphical mode, just type as regular user:\n"
"`setxkbmap -layout ua`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1887
msgid "To know more, read the man page for setxkbmap."
msgstr "Les mer om mannsiden for setxkbmap."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:1888
#, no-wrap
msgid "Install a printer"
msgstr "Installer en skriver"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1891
msgid "In Slint the CUPS print server manages printers and printing tasks. In its default configuration, recorded in the file /etc/cups/cupsd.conf, only users belonging to the `sys` (short for _system_) group are allowed to perform administrative tasks, like adding or removing a printer."
msgstr "I Slint CUPS print server behandler skrivere og utskrifter. I standardkonfigurasjonen oppført i filen /etc/cups/cupsd. Hvis bare brukere som tilhører `sys` (kort for _system_) gruppen får lov til å utføre administrative oppgaver, som å legge til eller fjerne en skriver."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1893
msgid "For a simple setup (printer attached to a desktop or laptop and not shared between machines), you just need to add one user (who will manage the printers) to the `sys` group. For instance adding the user didier_to the group `sys` can be done two ways:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1895
msgid "In console mode or using a terminal emulator, become root with `su -` then type:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1897
msgid "`gpasswd --add didier sys`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1899
msgid "In graphical mode from the Slint Control Center click on Users and Groups (System category), select the user and click Properties, then in the Groups tab check `sys`. Or the other way round (select the group then add the user to it)."
msgstr "I grafisk modus fra Slint Control Center klikk på brukere og grupper (Systemkategori), velg brukeren og klikk på Egenskaper, og deretter i gruppe-fanesjekken `sys`. Eller den andre runden (velg gruppen og deretter legg brukeren til den)."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1901
msgid "There are several ways to add and configure a printer (this has to be done by an user member of the group `sys`):"
msgstr "Det finnes flere måter å legge til og konfigurere en skriver (dette må gjøres av en bruker i gruppen `sys`):"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1903
msgid "From the Slint Control Center, category Hardware, click on Printer Setup to display a GUI allowing a simple setup..."
msgstr "Fra Slint Control Center, kategori Hardware, klikk på Printer oppsett for å vise et GUI noe enkelt oppsett..."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1904
msgid "... Or click on Cups Print Control the display a web interface to the CUPS server. You can also display the web interface to the CUPS server typing `localhost:631` in the address field of a web browser."
msgstr "... Eller klikk på oppskriving kontroll på visning av webgrensesnitt til CUPS-serveren. Du kan også vise webgrensesnittet til CUPS serveren som skriver `localhost:631` i adressefeltet til en nettleser."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1905
msgid "If you have a Hewlett Packard device, make a right click on the *hp* logo in the notification area of the panel."
msgstr "Hvis du har en Hewlett Pakkeenhet, gjør du et høyreklikk på *hp* -logoen i varslingsområdet for panelet."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1907
msgid "To make any print setting the CUPS server should be running. It is started when you start Slint if the service `cups` in checked among the System Services (it is checked by default in Slint)."
msgstr "For å foreta en utskriftsinnstilling bør CUPS serveren kjøre. Det er startet når du starter Slint hvis tjenesten `kopper` i haket av systemtjenestene (det er sjekket som standard i Slint)."

#. type: Title ===
#: HandBook.adoc:1908
#, no-wrap
msgid "Sound set up"
msgstr "Lyd konfigurert opp"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1911
msgid "In Slint applications either send their sound output either to ALSA or to PulseAudio."
msgstr "I Slint-applikasjoner sender enten sin lydutgang til ALSA eller til PulseAudio."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1913
msgid "In the latter case PulseAudio in turn sends the output stream to an ALSA mixer which direct it to the sound cards."
msgstr "I sistnevnte tilfelle sender PulseAudio en utgangstråle til en ALSA-blander som direkte den til lydkortene."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1915
msgid "As a result, a setting like an output sound volume can always be done by an ALSA mixer, and also by a PulseAudio mixer but only in case the application sends its sound output to PulseAudio."
msgstr "Derfor kan en innstilling som et utgangslydvolum alltid gjøres av en ALSA-blander. eller også av en lydmikser for puls, men bare hvis applikasjonen sender lydeffekten sin til PulseAudio."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1917
msgid "We will present now applications that can be used to modify the sound settings"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1918
#, no-wrap
msgid "pavucontrol (for PulseAudio)"
msgstr "Monteringsvæske (for pulsAudio)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1921
msgid "`pavucontrol` stands for PulseAudio Volume Control and is a graphical application. You can start it from a terminal or application menu, or doing a right click on the sound mixer icon on the top panel of Mate. Actually it allows more settings than just the volume control, take the time to explore all its features."
msgstr "`pavucontrol` står for PulseAudio Volumkontroll og er en grafisk applikasjon. Du kan starte det fra en terminal eller en programmeny, eller gjør et høyreklikk på ikonet til den lydblanderen på toppstykket i matten. Faktisk tillater det flere innstillinger enn volumkontrollen, ta deg tid til å utforske alle egenskapene."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1923
msgid "You can also use volume control applet in the notification area of the panel: a left click allows to adjust the volume, a right click gives access to other settings and allows to start the pavucontrol mixer."
msgstr "Du kan også bruke volumkontroll applet i området varsel i panelet: et venstreklikk lar deg justere volumet, et høyreklikk gir tilgang til andre innstillinger og gir mulighet til å starte basketrening."

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1926
#, no-wrap
msgid "alsamixer (for ALSA)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1929
msgid "alsamixer is a ncurses application, providing a semi-graphical user interface."
msgstr "alsamixer er et overvåkingsprogram, som gir et semegrafisk brukergrensesnitt."

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1931
msgid "To use it type in a console or in a graphical terminal:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1933
#, no-wrap
msgid "alsamixer\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1935
msgid "then:"
msgstr "Deretter:"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1937
msgid "Use the page up key to increase the volume by 5%"
msgstr "Bruk side opp tasten for å øke volumet med 5%"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1938
msgid "Use the page down key to decrease the volume by 5%"
msgstr "Bruk sidenasten for å redusere volumet med 5%"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1939
msgid "press Esc to leave the application."
msgstr "trykk Esc for å forlate applikasjonen."

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1940
#, no-wrap
msgid "amixer (for ALSA)"
msgstr "amixer (mot ALAT)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1942
msgid "The command is of the form:"
msgstr "Kommandoen er av skjemaet:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1944
#, no-wrap
msgid "amixer <arguments>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1946
msgid "For instance to set the main volume to 70% type:"
msgstr "For eksempel for å angi hovedvolumet til 70% type:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1948
#, no-wrap
msgid "amixer sset Master 70%\n"
msgstr "amixer sset Master 70\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1950
msgid "To know more, type one of these commands:"
msgstr "For å vite mer, skriv inn en av disse kommandoene:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1953
#, no-wrap
msgid "man amixer\n"
"amixer -h\n"
msgstr "mann amixer\n"
"amixer -h\n"

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1954
#, no-wrap
msgid "sam (the Speech-Friendly Alsa Mixer)"
msgstr "Sam (Speech-Friendly Alsa Mixer)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1959
#, no-wrap
msgid "sam allows selection of the sound card to work on when there are more than one such device in your machine.\n"
"When there is only one, it directly presents the different mixers for configuration."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1965
#, no-wrap
msgid "All selections, be it sound cards, mixers or a given feature of a\n"
" specific mixer are selected by scrolling through the available options using the up and down arrows, then entering on the desired one: +\n"
"`q` leave the selection list and/or quits. +\n"
"`Shift-q` exits the program from anywhere. +\n"
"`F1` Displays any extra information if available.\n"
msgstr "Alle valg, vær lydkort, blandere eller en gitt funksjon av en\n"
" -spesifikk blander velges ved å bla gjennom tilgjengelige alternativer ved hjelp av opp- og ned-pilene, deretter skrive det inn på ønsket navn: +\n"
"`k` lar valglisten og/eller lagre. +\n"
"`Shift-q` forlater programmet fra hvor som helst. +\n"
"`F1` Viser ekstra informasjon hvis tilgjengelig.\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1973
msgid "When the name of the desired option is known, one can instead press its first letter. First-letter navigation is case-insensitive.  That will then take you to the first selection starting with the pressed letter. Pressing the same letter again, will move you to the next option starting with that letter if more than one option like that exists.  Repeating the letter will cycle among all those options starting with that letter."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1978
#, no-wrap
msgid "The settable features of a mixer can be listed pressing F1.\n"
"They are presented as a selection list, showing briefly all relevant information, e.g. \"playback volume down from 84 percent\" is the option to lower the playback volume setting. As you can see, it also tells you what the current setting is."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1980
msgid "sam does not work correctly in a graphical terminal. Use it in a console."
msgstr "Slam fungerer ikke riktig i en grafisk terminal. Bruk den i en konsoll."

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1981
#, no-wrap
msgid "pamixer and ponymix (for PulseAudio)"
msgstr "pamixer og ponymix (for PulseAudio)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1983
msgid "These utilities are similar, with commands in this form:"
msgstr ""

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1986
#, no-wrap
msgid "pamixer <arguments>\n"
"ponymix <arguments>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1988
msgid "For instance to set the volume to 70% for the default sink type one of these commands:"
msgstr "For eksempel å sette volumet til 70% for standard type for en av disse kommandoene:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1991
#, no-wrap
msgid "pamixer --set-volume 7\n"
"ponymix set-volume 7O\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:1993
msgid "To know more, type:"
msgstr "For å vite mer, type:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:1996
#, no-wrap
msgid "pamixer -h\n"
"ponymix --help\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ====
#: HandBook.adoc:1998
#, no-wrap
msgid "pacmd and pactl (for PulseAudio)"
msgstr "pacmd og kvist (for PulseAudio)"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:2001
msgid "Both of these command line applications control a running PulseAudio daemon."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:2003
msgid "pacmd typed alone brings up an interactive dialog. Press Ctrl+d to exit from it but do not type exit, as that would kill PulseAudio!"
msgstr "pacmd skrevet alene gir en interaktiv dialog. Trykk Ctrl+d for å forlate den, men ikke skrive, siden det ville drepe PulseAudio!"

#. type: Plain text
#: HandBook.adoc:2005 HandBook.adoc:2035
msgid "To know more:"
msgstr "Vil du vite mer:"

#. type: delimited block -
#: HandBook.adoc:2010
#, no-wrap
msgid "man pactl\n"
"man pacmd\n"
"pactl --help\n"
"pacmd --help\n"
